'''''Sarcophyton glaucum''''', also known as '''rough leather coral''', is a common species of [[Alcyonacea|soft coral]] found from the [[Red Sea]] to western Pacific Ocean. It grows up to 80&nbsp;cm usually on reef flats, in lagoons and on seaward slopes.<ref>{{cite book | title=Coral reef guide. Red Sea | first1=Ewald | last1=Lieske | first2=Robert | last2=Myers | year=2004 | page=248 | isbn=9780007741731}}</ref><ref>[http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=209621 WoRMS - World Register of Marine Species - Sarcophyton glaucum (Quoy & Gaimard, 1833)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://eol.org/pages/323291/overview Leather Coral (Sarcophyton glaucum) - Information on Leather Coral - Encyclopedia of Life<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

